<paragraph id="8BBC1335B07B691442C37F770185FC81" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1226]" box="[219,664,815,841]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">Queens, males and ecology unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC1335B07B691442C37F08017DFB02" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,1226]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">
T a x o n o m i c n o t e s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B691443E77F080198FCA1" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[511,645,847,873]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B691443E77F080198FCA1" box="[511,645,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the most resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B6914419E7F080743FCA1" authorityName="Pisarski" authorityYear="1967" box="[902,1118,847,873]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B6914419E7F080743FCA1" box="[902,1118,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing with the latter the character of sculpture on the first gastral tergite. Moreover, 
<typeStatus id="54B8AD97B07B691446797F3707D5FC41" box="[1121,1224,879,905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54B8AD97B07B691442C47FC8025FFC62" box="[220,322,912,938]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">paratype</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B691443F67FC8016CFC61" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[494,625,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B691443F67FC8016CFC61" box="[494,625,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were originally included by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF926EC4B07B691441D07FD70767FC62" author="Pisarski, B." box="[968,1146,911,938]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" pagination="375 - 425" refId="ref15414" refString="Pisarski, B. Fourmis (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) d'Afganistan recoltes par Dr. Lindberg // Annales Zoologici. - 1967. - 24, 6. - P. 375 - 425." type="book chapter" year="1967">Pisarski (1967)</bibRefCitation>
to the 
<typeStatus id="54B8AD97B07B691442BE7FE80211FC02" box="[166,268,944,970]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">paratype</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B6914439C7FE80146FC01" authorityName="Pisarski" authorityYear="1967" box="[388,603,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B6914439C7FE80146FC01" box="[388,603,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, Pisarski (loc. cit., p. 405) noted that “Workers from Hassan 
<collectingRegion id="49C7DDD7B07B691443DE7F97010AFC21" box="[454,535,975,1001]" country="Iran" name="Gilan" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">Guilan</collectingRegion>
have somewhat coarser, but more regular sculpture than those from Cheikhabad” (out translation from French). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B691441277FA800DDFBC1" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[831,960,1007,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B691441277FA800DDFBC1" box="[831,960,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinctly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B691442BE78480262FBE1" authorityName="Pisarski" authorityYear="1967" box="[166,383,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B691442BE78480262FBE1" box="[166,383,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the sculpture of mesosoma and waist: the mesosomal dorsum is with more regular, almost straight longitudinal rugae, the waist dorsum is with regular longitudinally-concentric rugae 
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B6914403378080154FBA1" box="[555,585,1104,1129]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">vs.</emphasis>
the mesosomal and waist dorsum are with sinuous longitudinal rugae in the latter species. Additionally, longitudinal rugosity on the head dorsum in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B6914433E78C802BBFB61" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[294,422,1167,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B6914433E78C802BBFB61" box="[294,422,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less coarse, number of rugae between frontal carinae level with the eyes ≥ 20 (≤ 
<quantity id="4CFBBED0B07B6914432278F70268FB01" box="[314,373,1199,1226]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.81" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" unit="in" value="15.0">15 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B07B6914436478E80152FB01" authorityName="Pisarski" authorityYear="1967" box="[380,591,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B07B6914436478E80152FB01" box="[380,591,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
